description: Manage Java projects in Visual Studio Code
contributes.commands.java.project.addLib: Add a jar file or a folder to project classpath
contributes.commands.java.project.remove: Remove jar file from project classpath
configuration.java.dependency.showMember: Show the members in the explorer
configuration.java.dependency.syncWithFo: Synchronize Java Projects explorer selection with folder explorer
configuration.java.dependency.autoRefres: Synchronize Java Projects explorer with changes
configuration.java.dependency.refreshDel: The delay time (ms) the auto refresh is invoked when changes are detected
configuration.java.dependency.packagePre: Package presentation mode: flat or hierarchical
configuration.java.project.exportJar.tar: Specifies the output path of export jar. The default value is `"${workspaceFolder}/${workspaceFolderBasename}.jar"`. To select the output location manually each time exporting the jar file, simply leave it as `""` or set it to `"askUser"`.
taskDefinitions.java.project.exportJar.l: The label of export jar task.
taskDefinitions.java.project.exportJar.e: The content list of the exported jar.
taskDefinitions.java.project.exportJar.m: The main class in the manifest of the exported jar.
taskDefinitions.java.project.exportJar.t: The output path of the exported jar. This will override configuration.java.project.exportJar.targetPath.
taskDefinitions.java.project.exportJar.c: The folders containing output class files in the runtime scope.
taskDefinitions.java.project.exportJar.t: The folders containing output class files in the test scope.
taskDefinitions.java.project.exportJar.d: The artifact dependencies in the runtime scope.
taskDefinitions.java.project.exportJar.t: The artifact dependencies in the test scope.
